race.comment: OUR PARAMOUR (7) missed the placings two runs ago and then was 3 lengths from the winner in sixth-place over 1600m at Cranbourne last start. She will be peaking fourth up from a spell, and can figure in the top 3 over a middle distance. MOTIVER (2) was a fair eighth over 1600m at Sandown-Lakeside when fresh from a spell there nearly 3 weeks ago. She steps up in distance today against easier opposition and won't be far away. FIERY DEAL (13) was on the pace and fought on gamely for second over 1856m at Kyneton 17 days ago. She will keep on improving as she gets out over more ground, and she can take this out. MARINE EMPRESS (10) capped off some good form with a well-deserved win by a short-head at Werribee 3 weeks ago. She is bred to relish the extra 400m, and she can repeat the dose.
